==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Checkers
<hw>Check"ers</hw> <pr>(ch⟦ecr⟧k"⟦etil⟧rz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Checher</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>A game, called
also <altname>draughts</altname>, played on a checkerboard by two
persons, each having twelve men (counters or checkers) which are moved
diagonally. The game is ended when either of the players has lost all
his men, or can not move them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Checkerwork</ent>⟦br⟧
